    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-16T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-16T15:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1036: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Chairman of the American Delegation (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1"
                            type="to">Gibson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-16T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 16, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>104. Special for <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">Gibson</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>. Your 169, May 13, 4 p.m., from
                    London.</p>
                <p>When Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BSA1">Baldwin</persName> made suggestion as to
                    capital ships contained in your Section 4, did either of you inform him (<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>) as to the position taken by the American Delegation at
                    London in 1930,<note n="11" xml:id="d84fn11">See telegram No. 35, February 4,
                        from the Chairman of the American delegation, <ref
                            target="frus1930v01#pg_13">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1930, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 13</ref>; and telegram No. 212, April
                        10, from the Chairman of the American delegation, <ref
                            target="frus1930v01#pg_106">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 106</ref>.</note> (<hi rend="italic"
                        >b</hi>) as to my recent statements on the subject in Geneva or (<hi
                        rend="italic">c</hi>) as to the functions capital ships are now performing
                    in respect to the Far East? Please immediately send full details and his reply
                    if any.</p>
                <p>Did you gather that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BSA1">Baldwin</persName>’s failure
                    to include submarines in his list of weapons to be abolished was an over-sight
                    or intentional; if intentional, did he give any explanation therefor?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
